{"title_page": "Scissor Sisters (convicted killers)", "text_new": "{{Other uses|Scissor Sisters (disambiguation)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2013}}\n{{BLP sources|date=July 2018}}\n{{Infobox criminal\n|name= Linda and Charlotte Mulhall\n|image= \n|caption= \n|alias= The Scissor Sisters\n|birth_name = \n|birth_date= {{birth year and age|1975}} (Linda) <br/>c. 1983 (age 34-35) (Charlotte)\n|birth_place= [[Dublin]], [[Ireland]]\n|death_date= \n|cause=\n|victims= 1\n|beginyear=\n|endyear= \n| nationality = Irish\n| conviction_penalty = [[life imprisonment]] (Charlotte)<br/>15 years' imprisonment (Linda)\n| conviction_status = Incarcerated at [[Limerick Prison]] (Charlotte)<br/>Released (Linda)\n|apprehended= October 2006\n|conviction=  [[murder]] (Charlotte)<br/>[[manslaughter]] (Linda)\n|sentence    = \n|weapons     = [[Stanley knife]], hammer\n}}\n{{Location map | Ireland Central Dublin\n| relief   = yes\n| width    = 250\n| caption  = Location of the murder site in Dublin\n| lat_deg = 53.357842\n| lon_deg = -6.249823 \n| label   = 17 Richmond Cottages\n}}\n\n'''Linda and Charlotte Mulhall''' (also called the '''''Scissor Sisters''''' by the media) are sisters from [[Dublin]], Ireland, known for having killed and dismembered their mother's boyfriend, Farah Swaleh Noor, in March 2005. Noor was killed with a [[Stanley knife]] wielded by Charlotte and struck with a hammer by Linda following a confrontation with the sisters and their mother, Kathleen Mulhall. His head and penis were sliced off and the rest of his corpse dismembered by the women and dumped in [[Dublin]]'s [[Royal Canal]] where a piece of leg still wearing a sock was spotted floating near [[Croke Park]] ten days later.\n\nThe subsequent manhunt and the trial in October 2006 attracted intense media attention in Ireland as the true details of the crime slowly emerged. The sisters and their mother were arrested but released until Linda confessed to involvement in the crime. Kathleen Mulhall left the country at this point to live in England. When Charlotte and Linda were charged with murder in December 2005, their father, John Mulhall, hanged himself in [[Phoenix Park]]. As a result of the method they used to carry out the killing of Farah Swaleh Noor, Linda and Charlotte Mulhall were dubbed the ''Scissor Sisters'' by the media, after the pop rock band the [[Scissor Sisters]].<ref name=\"'Scissor' mother dated rapist after fleeing to UK\"/><ref name=\"Lengthy sentences for brutal sibling slayers\"/><ref name=\"Scissor Sister reveals head put in bins in Phoenix Park\"/> Justice [[Paul Carney]], presiding over the trial, said during sentencing that it was \"the most grotesque killing that has occurred in my professional lifetime\".<ref name=\"A horror story born out of dysfunction\"/> Charlotte Mulhall was given the mandatory life sentence and Linda Mulhall was given a 15-year sentence for manslaughter, with both being sent to [[D\u00f3chas Centre|Mountjoy Women's prison]] in Dublin.\n\nNoor's head and penis were never recovered,<ref name=\"Mulhall sister sentenced to life (2)\"/> although Linda later admitted they had put the head in rubbish bins around Phoenix Park. It was also thought that they carried the head by bus to [[Tallaght]] and buried it in a field, with Linda returning later to dig it up, carry it to another field using her son's schoolbag, smash it further with a hammer and bury it again. Linda attracted further media attention when she slit her wrists and was [[sectioned]]. Charlotte also attracted media attention when a photograph of her holding a knife to a male prisoner's throat was published; that action resulted in an increased security presence in all Irish prisons and Charlotte was moved from Mountjoy to [[Limerick]]. Kathleen Mulhall voluntarily returned to Ireland in February 2008 and faced several charges. She pleaded guilty to helping clean up the crime scene to conceal evidence and was sentenced to five years in prison in May 2009.\n\nThe case has resulted in several books and has been examined in at least one television series. It was said by the ''[[Irish Independent]]''{{'}}s legal affairs correspondent Dearbhail McDonald to have \"fuelled fears of ritual killings in Ireland\".<ref name=\"Lengthy sentences for brutal sibling slayers\"/>\n\n==Mulhall family background==\nThe Mulhalls were from Kilclare Gardens, a working class area in [[Tallaght]], south [[Dublin]]. Their parents John and Kathleen Mulhall raised a family of three boys and three girls. John Mulhall allegedly abused Kathleen. Their marriage broke down and Kathleen entered into a relationship with Farah Swaleh Noor in 2002. Noor moved into their family home with Kathleen, and John Mulhall took some of his children and moved out. He rented various accommodations in Dublin over a period of a year, then moved back into the home after Kathleen left and moved to [[Cork (city)|Cork]] with Noor. Kathleen and Noor returned to Dublin in 2004. Noor allegedly subjected Kathleen Mulhall to regular beatings.<ref name=\"Mulhall sister admits she hit victim with hammer\">{{cite web|url=http://www.breakingnews.ie/archives/2006/1018/ireland/cwidkfojeyql |title=Mulhall sister admits she hit victim with hammer|date=18 October 2006 |publisher=breakingnews.ie |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110614133636/http://www.breakingnews.ie/archives/2006/1018/ireland/cwidkfojeyql/ |archivedate=14 June 2011 |accessdate=2 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Composure breaks down as court hears litany of violence and abuse\">{{cite news|url=http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/ireland/2009/0506/1224245993737.html|title=Composure breaks down as court hears litany of violence and abuse|date=6 May 2009|accessdate=4 September 2009|newspaper=[[The Irish Times]]}}</ref>\n\n===Linda Mulhall===\nLinda Mulhall was 30 years old at the time of the killing. She was unemployed, had left school early and had four children. The relationship with the father of her children broke up<ref name=\"Fianc\u00e9 at the centre of 'Scissor Sister' attack\">{{cite news|author=Mick McCaffrey Security Editor |url=http://www.tribune.ie/archive/article/2007/jun/10/fiance-at-the-centre-of-scissor-sister-attack/ |title=Fianc\u00e9 at the centre of 'Scissor Sister' attack |date=10 June 2007 |accessdate=4 September 2009 |newspaper=[[Sunday Tribune]] }}{{dead link|date=June 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> and she got into another relationship with an individual called Wayne Kinsella who subsequently abused them, in one case beating the children with [[Electrical_conduit#Flexible | an electrical flex]]. The abuse was later investigated, and the children were taken into care by the social services, while Wayne Kinsella served a six-year prison sentence for his cruelty to the children. Kinsella himself had an extremely violent history, having been thrown out of school for violent behaviour, according to his elder sister, Donna. In a 2013 [[RT\u00c9 Radio]] interview, Donna Kinsella said that her brother Wayne was always an extremely violent person, even during his childhood, and stated that he used to beat members of his own family, including his parents, and had broken her jaw on one occasion.<ref name=\"Don't ever let my double-killer brother out of jail\">{{cite web|author=Conor Feehan Security Editor|url=http://www.herald.ie/news/dont-ever-let-my-doublekiller-brother-out-of-jail/|title='Don't ever let my double-killer brother out of jail'|date=22 May 2013|accessdate=14 September 2016|publisher=[[Herald]]}}</ref>  In May 1996, Kinsella received an eight-year prison sentence for the murder of a retired auctioneer, Thomas Foreman, who was killed while visiting his wife's grave in [[Glasnevin Cemetery]] in Dublin on 23 September 1995. In May 2012, Kinsella was jailed for life after being found guilty of the murder of 29-year-old Dubliner Adil Essalhi, who was stabbed to death in a field near [[Tyrrelstown]] on 6 January 2011. Kinsella claimed he murdered Adil Essalhi, because he believed that Mr. Essalhi had been involved in the killing of his younger brother, Lee Kinsella, who was shot dead in [[Finglas]] in May 2006.<ref name=\"Wayne Kinsella convicted of murder of Adel Essalhi in Tyrrelstown\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rte.ie/news/2012/0521/321799-wayne-kinsella-convicted-of-murder-of-adel-essalhi/|title=Wayne Kinsella convicted of murder of Adel Essalhi in Tyrrelstown|date=21 May 2012|accessdate=28 June 2019|website=[[RT\u00c9]]}}</ref> Wayne's sister Donna said Mr. Essalhi had nothing to do with Lee's death.<ref name=\"Don't ever let my double-killer brother out of jail\">{{cite web|author=Conor Feehan Security Editor|url=http://www.herald.ie/news/dont-ever-let-my-doublekiller-brother-out-of-jail/|title='Don't ever let my double-killer brother out of jail'|date=22 May 2013|accessdate=14 September 2016|publisher=[[Herald]]}}</ref> Wayne Kinsella's nephew Michael Kinsella would later be jailed for 15 years in May 2016 for helping his uncle kill Mr. Essalhi. Linda Mulhall, meanwhile, had a history of alcohol abuse and suffered from an addiction to heroin. She had one previous conviction in 1993 for [[larceny]].<ref name=\"A horror story born out of dysfunction\">{{cite news|author=CONOR LALLY, Crime Correspondent|url=http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/ireland/2009/0509/1224246189748.html|title=A horror story born out of dysfunction|date=9 May 2009|accessdate=4 September 2009|newspaper=[[The Irish Times]]}}</ref>\n\n===Charlotte Mulhall===\nCharlotte Mulhall was 21 years old when the killing took place. Like her sister, she had a history of drug and alcohol abuse. She had a number of minor previous convictions for criminal damage and public order offences and was charged with criminal damage and given the [[Probation]] Act in October 2005. She was also involved in prostitution.<ref name=\"Mulhall sister sentenced to life\">{{cite web|url=http://www.breakingnews.ie/ireland/?jp=CWIDQLSNKFAU&rss=yes|title=Mulhall sister sentenced to life|date=4 December 2006|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=breakingnews.ie}}</ref>\n\nDuring their trial, [[garda\u00ed]] described the girls' upbringing as \"troubled and tough\".<ref name=\"Verdicts returned in canal murder trial\">{{cite web|url=http://www.choicefm.ie/news_details.php|title=Verdicts returned in canal murder trial|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=[[Choice FM]]}}</ref>\n\n==Farah Swaleh Noor==\n<!-- [[File:Farahswaleh.jpg|right|180px|thumb|Photograph of Farah Swaleh Noor released during the garda investigation into his death]] -->\n\n{{Infobox person\n|name=Farah Swaleh Noor\n| birth_date = 1965\n| birth_place = [[Mombasa]], \n [[Kenya]]\n| death_place= [[Northside, Dublin|Summerhill]], [[Dublin]], Ireland\n| death_date = 20 March 2005 (aged 40)\n| body_discovered = [[Royal Canal (Ireland)|Royal Canal]]\n| occupation = unemployed\n}}\n\nFarah Swaleh Noor was 40 years old at the time of his death. He arrived in Ireland in December 1996, claiming to be a [[Somalis|Somali]] called \"Sheilila Salim\" whose family had been killed in [[Mogadishu]] during the [[Somali Civil War]]. Subsequent investigations revealed that he was in fact [[Kenya]]n and that his family was still alive. Farah was ethnically [[Somalis|Somali]]. The [[Department of Justice and Equality|Department of Justice, Equality and Law Reform]] ordered that he be deported but he appealed and was granted Irish citizenship in March 1999 on grounds he became the father of an Irish-born child. He had four previous convictions for offences including [[Substance intoxication|intoxication]], threatening and abusive behaviour and assault. In 1997, he [[rape]]d a mentally disabled 16-year-old Chinese girl. She later gave birth to a son. Two other women had children by him and both described having been raped by him.<ref name=\"Woman tells canal body murder trial of rape hell\">{{cite news|author=Eleanor Burnhill|url=http://www.independent.ie/national-news/woman-tells-canal-body-murder-trial-of-rape-hell-74802.html|title=Woman tells canal body murder trial of rape hell|date=24 October 2006|accessdate=4 September 2009|newspaper=[[Irish Independent]]}}</ref> Noor had faced eight charges of disorder and assault, one involving a sexual assault in which a knife was found at the scene by garda\u00ed. He was convicted on three occasions but never served time in jail. Noor lived in a number of areas in Dublin, including [[D\u00fan Laoghaire]] and [[Firhouse]], as well as the inner city before moving in with Kathleen Mulhall. Garda\u00ed described him as being particularly [[Domestic violence|violent towards women]].<ref name=\"African drifter died after drink and drugs bender\">{{cite news|author=Eleanor Burnhill|url=http://www.independent.ie/lifestyle/african-drifter-died-after--drink-and-drugs-bender-1466364.html|title=African drifter died after drink and drugs bender|date=24 October 2006|accessdate=4 September 2008|newspaper=[[Irish Independent]]}}</ref>\n\n==Events surrounding the killing==\nThe killing took place at a flat Kathleen Mulhall was renting in a house on Richmond Cottages, [[Summerhill, Dublin|Summerhill]], on 20 March 2005. This was on the bank holiday of [[Saint Patrick's Day|Saint Patrick's weekend]].<ref name=\"Mulhall sister sentenced to life (1)\">{{cite web|url=http://www.breakingnews.ie/ireland/?jp=CWIDQLSNKFAU&rss=yes#ixzz0PsHAZfe|title=Mulhall sister sentenced to life|date=4 December 2006|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=breakingnews.ie}}</ref>\n\n===Build-up to the killing===\nOn the day of the killing, Linda, Charlotte, their mother and Farah Swaleh Noor had been drinking heavily in Dublin city centre. Farah bought [[vodka]] and Kathleen Mulhall purchased [[Coca-Cola]] which they drank as they walked around the city before stopping on the [[River Liffey]] Boardwalk where Charlotte and her mother took [[Ecstasy (drug)|ecstasy tablets]]. They returned to Kathleen Mulhall's flat where the women took ecstasy. Kathleen Mulhall crushed a tablet into the victim's drink so they were \"all on\" the same \"buzz\".<ref name=\"Mulhall sister sentenced to life (2)\">{{cite web|url=http://www.breakingnews.ie/ireland/?jp=CWIDQLSNKFAU&rss=yes#ixzz0PwMQ2LM2|title=Mulhall sister sentenced to life|date=4 December 2006|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=breakingnews.ie}}</ref>\n\n===Death of Farah Swaleh Noor===\nLinda and Noor were sitting on a two-seater couch with Charlotte sitting on the arm, when Noor started touching Linda in a sexual way. He spoke into her ear, put his arms around her waist and refused to let her go. Kathleen then started screaming at him and a verbal altercation took place where Kathleen Mulhall was alleged to have instructed them to \"just kill him for me\". Charlotte picked up a [[Stanley knife]] and struck Noor across the throat, inflicting a wound that sent him to the ground. Linda then picked up a hammer and hit him on the head a number of times. Their mother looked on but did not participate. Noor was stabbed at least 27 times. It may have been more, but [[pathologist]]s had no opportunity to examine the full body.<ref name=\"From murder to manslaughter\">{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/national-news/from-murder-to-manslaughter-75843.html|title=From murder to manslaughter|date=30 October 2006|accessdate=4 September 2009|newspaper=[[Irish Independent]]}}</ref>\n\n===Dismemberment and disposal of the corpse===\nLinda and Charlotte then dragged Noor's corpse into the bathroom where they began to dismember the remains. Noor's head, [[limb (anatomy)|limb]]s and [[penis]] were severed using a kitchen knife and hammer. They put towels over his legs to stem the flow of blood. The dismemberment took a number of hours and the body parts were placed in black plastic bags and a sports bag before being disposed of in the [[Royal Canal]]. This took the three women several trips. They decided not to throw the head in to prevent identification. The head was brought by bus to Tallaght where they walked through [[The Square, Tallaght|The Square Shopping Centre]] to Tymon North Park. They walked to where Charlotte dug a hole with a knife to bury the head. Kathleen Mulhall threw the knives and the hammer into a nearby pond. A number of days later, Linda Mulhall allegedly returned to the park and dug up the head. Using her son's schoolbag, she transferred it to a field in the Killinarden Estate, Tallaght, where she broke it up with a hammer before burying it again.<ref name=\"Mulhall sister admits she hit victim with hammer\" />\n\n==Garda S\u00edoch\u00e1na investigation==\nThe killing only came to light ten days later when Noor's leg, with a sock on the end, was seen floating in the canal, a few hundred yards from [[Croke Park]]. [[Garda Water Unit|Garda sub-aqua divers]] retrieved most of the rest of his body in seven parts. Garda\u00ed traced his identity through media appeals. Noor was only identified when someone recognised a T-shirt on the recovered torso. That key witness, a Somalian man who was the first to connect the missing Noor with the three Mulhall women, was paid a \"substantial\" reward by Crimestoppers.<ref name=\"Gardai seek mother of killer sisters\"/> Noor's head and penis were never found.<ref name=\"Mulhall sister sentenced to life (2)\"/>\n\nThe sisters and their parents were arrested in August but denied any knowledge of the killing. A number of weeks later Linda contacted investigating officers admitting her involvement. Garda\u00ed took a voluntary statement from her at her home in Tallaght in August 2005. Until this, Garda\u00ed had been making limited progress in the case. When Garda\u00ed searched the Mulhall flat in Summerhill, they found bloodstains that were later confirmed to match Noor's [[DNA]].<ref name=\"Mulhall sister admits she hit victim with hammer\" /><ref name=\"Gardai seek mother of killer sisters\">{{cite news|author=Enda Leahy|url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/world/ireland/article616939.ece|title=Gardai seek mother of killer sisters|date=29 October 2006|accessdate=4 September 2009|newspaper=[[The Sunday Times]]}}</ref> After Linda's confession, Kathleen Mulhall fled the country in September 2005 and garda\u00ed were unable to locate her again until January 2008. She was living in England.<ref name=\"'Scissor' mother dated rapist after fleeing to UK\">{{cite news|author=Mick McCaffrey and Mark Hilliard |url=http://www.tribune.ie/news/article/2009/may/10/scissor-mother-dated-rapist-after-fleeing-to-uk/ |title='Scissor' mother dated rapist after fleeing to UK |date=10 May 2009 |accessdate=4 September 2009 |newspaper=[[Sunday Tribune]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090515084041/http://www.tribune.ie/news/article/2009/may/10/scissor-mother-dated-rapist-after-fleeing-to-uk/ |archivedate=15 May 2009 }}</ref>\n\n==Court cases==\n===Murder trial of Linda and Charlotte Mulhall===\nLinda and Charlotte were both charged with murder and pleaded not guilty in the [[High Court (Ireland)|Central Criminal Court]]. Their trial took place in October 2006 with Linda Mulhall being found guilty of [[manslaughter]] while her sister Charlotte was found guilty of the murder of Noor. Linda's jury accepted her defence of provocation.\n\nCharlotte Mulhall was given the mandatory life sentence and Linda Mulhall was given a 15-year sentence for manslaughter. The judge argued that Linda, a heroin addict, had initially tried to halt the trial by refusing to take [[methadone]]. Leave to appeal was refused for both sentences.<ref name=\"Mulhall sister sentenced to life\">{{cite web|url=http://www.breakingnews.ie/ireland/?jp=CWIDQLSNKFAU&rss=yes#ixzz0PwMD7wOo|title=Mulhall sister sentenced to life|date=4 December 2006|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=breakingnews.ie}}</ref><ref name=\"Sisters sentenced over Noor death\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rte.ie/news/2006/1204/noorf.html|title=Sisters sentenced over Noor death|date=4 December 2008|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=[[Raidi\u00f3 Teilif\u00eds \u00c9ireann|RT\u00c9]]}}</ref>\n\nLinda Mulhall appealed the severity of her sentence<ref name=\"D.P.P.-v- Linda Mulhall\">{{cite web|url=http://www.courts.ie/Judgments.nsf/23fd4a34bad801d980256ec50047a0a8/67a09b519186ab01802573ee00523b66?OpenDocument&Highlight=0,mulhall|title=D.P.P.-v- Linda Mulhall|date=8 February 2008|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=[[Criminal Court Record of Appeals]]}}</ref> on the grounds that it was passed without psychiatric and probation reports. This appeal failed, with the [[Court of Criminal Appeal]] finding the sentence to be appropriate.<ref name=\"Mulhall loses appeal over jail sentence\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rte.ie/news/2008/0421/noor.html?rss|title=Mulhall loses appeal over jail sentence|date=21 April 2008|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=[[Raidi\u00f3 Teilif\u00eds \u00c9ireann|RT\u00c9]]}}</ref>\n\nCharlotte Mulhall requested leave to appeal her conviction on the grounds that Justice Carney had put pressure on the jury to reach a verdict even though the foreman had indicated they were deadlocked.<ref name=\"Charlotte Mulhall begins murder conviction appeal\">{{cite news|url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/breaking-news/ireland/charlotte-mulhall-begins-murder-conviction-appeal-13392822.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130420073056/http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/breaking-news/ireland/charlotte-mulhall-begins-murder-conviction-appeal-13392822.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=20 April 2013 |title=Charlotte Mulhall begins murder conviction appeal |date=11 March 2008 |accessdate=4 September 2009 |newspaper=[[The Belfast Telegraph]] }}</ref> This failed on the grounds that the defence did not raise objections to the comments during the trial and the fact that the jury was not affected by any alleged undue pressure to reach a verdict.<ref name=\"Charlotte Mulhall denied leave to appeal\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rte.ie/news/2008/0311/noorfs.html|title=Charlotte Mulhall denied leave to appeal|date=11 March 2008|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=[[Raidi\u00f3 Teilif\u00eds \u00c9ireann|RT\u00c9]]}}</ref>\n\n===Court case against Kathleen Mulhall===\nKathleen Mulhall voluntarily returned to Ireland in February 2008 and was charged with, among other offences, two counts of giving false information to garda\u00ed about Noor's whereabouts, and withholding information which she \"knew or believed\" would be of assistance in prosecuting her daughters for Noor's murder. She was also charged with impeding an arrest in the murder investigation. She pleaded guilty to helping to clean up the crime scene to conceal evidence.<ref name=\"Mulhall cleaned up murder crime scene\">{{cite news|url=http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/breaking/2009/0505/breaking52.htm|title=Mulhall cleaned up murder crime scene|date=5 May 2009|accessdate=4 September 2009|newspaper=[[The Irish Times]]}}</ref><ref name=\"Scissor Sisters' mum faces 10 new charges\">{{cite news|author=Fiach Kelly|url=http://www.independent.ie/national-news/scissor-sisters-mum-faces-10-new-charges-1321949.html|title=Scissor Sisters' mum faces 10 new charges|date=20 March 2008|accessdate=4 September 2009|newspaper=[[Irish Independent]]}}</ref> Kathleen Mulhall was sentenced to five years in prison in May 2009.<ref name=\"Mulhall sentenced for cleaning crime scene\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rte.ie/news/2009/0508/mulhallk.html|title=Mulhall sentenced for cleaning crime scene|date=8 May 2009|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=[[Raidi\u00f3 Teilif\u00eds \u00c9ireann|RT\u00c9]]}}</ref>\n\n==Fallout and aftermath==\n===Mulhall family===\nThe girls' father, John Mulhall, hanged himself in [[Phoenix Park]] when his daughters were charged with the killing in December 2005. He was not believed to have been involved in the killing.<ref name=\"Lengthy sentences for brutal sibling slayers\">{{cite news|author=Dearbhail McDonaldLegal Affairs|url=http://www.independent.ie/national-news/lengthy-sentences-for-brutal-sibling-slayers-63017.html#Scene_1|title=Lengthy sentences for brutal sibling slayers|date=12 May 2006|accessdate=4 September 2009|newspaper=[[Irish Independent]]}}</ref>\n\nLinda Mulhall turned to alcohol and slashed her arms, causing her to spend over a week in a psychiatric hospital.<ref name=\"Mulhall sister admits she hit victim with hammer\" /> In April 2009, she claimed to fellow inmates that she had in fact smashed Noor's head and distributed the fragments in rubbish bins in the [[Phoenix Park]].<ref name=\"Scissor Sister reveals head put in bins in Phoenix Park\">{{cite news|author=Cormac Looney |url=http://www.herald.ie/national-news/city-news/scissor-sister-reveals-head-put-in-bins-in-phoenix-park-1707808.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130217193754/http://www.herald.ie/national-news/city-news/scissor-sister-reveals-head-put-in-bins-in-phoenix-park-1707808.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=17 February 2013 |title=Scissor Sister reveals head put in bins in Phoenix Park |date=14 April 2009 |accessdate=4 September 2009 |newspaper=[[Evening Herald]] }}</ref> This first disclosure of where Noor's head had ended up, was referred to as \"the final secret of the Scissor Sisters\" by Cormac Looney in the ''[[Evening Herald]]''.<ref name=\"Scissor Sister reveals head put in bins in Phoenix Park\"/>\n\nCharlotte caused a further national controversy in 2008 when photographs of her jokingly holding a knife to the throat of a male prisoner in [[Mountjoy Prison]] were leaked to the press. As a result, security in Irish prisons was increased.<ref name=\"Prison Service to up security over Scissor Sister pictures\">{{cite news|author=Shane Phelan|url=http://www.independent.ie/national-news/prison-service-to-up-security-over-scissor-sister-pictures-1461724.html#Scene_1|title=Prison Service to up security over Scissor Sister pictures|date=23 August 2008|accessdate=4 September 2009|newspaper=[[Irish Independent]]}}</ref> and Charlotte was moved to [[Limerick Prison]], the only other Irish prison to contain a women's unit.\n\nThe girls' brother, James Mulhall, pleaded guilty to the robbery of two prostitutes, claiming he robbed the women to support his own six children and his sister Linda's four children whom he took on after she was jailed.<ref name=\"Two men get five years for robbing prostitutes\">{{cite web|url=http://www.breakingnews.ie/archives/2008/0401/ireland/mhojojgbkfmh/|title=Two men get five years for robbing prostitutes|date=1 April 2008|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=breakingnews.ie}}</ref>\n\n===Books===\nThe case received a high amount of attention due to the grotesque and macabre nature of the crime. This led to the sisters being dubbed \"The Scissor Sisters\" by the media after the [[Scissor Sisters|pop group]] from New York, USA.\n\nSeveral books were written on the circumstances surrounding the death of Farah Swaleh Noor:\n*''The Torso in the Canal''&nbsp;\u2014 John Mooney (Maverick House, {{ISBN|978-1-905379-38-5}})\n*''The Irish Scissor Sisters''&nbsp;\u2014 Mick McCaffrey (Merlin Publishing, {{ISBN|1-903582-72-5}})<ref name=\"'Scissor' mother dated rapist after fleeing to UK\"/> McCaffrey covered the case for the ''[[Sunday Tribune]]''.<ref name=\"'Scissor' mother dated rapist after fleeing to UK\"/>\n\n===Television series===\nThe 2009 RT\u00c9 television series ''Killers'' featured the Mulhall sisters.<ref name=\"Lifestyle rubbish and lame-brained comedy jostle for position with four-part tale of man who rescued seahorses\">{{cite news|author=John Boland|url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/tv-radio/lifestyle-rubbish-and-lamebrained-comedy-jostle-for-position-with-fourpart-tale-of-man-who-rescued-seahorses-1859824.html|title=Lifestyle rubbish and lame-brained comedy jostle for position with four-part tale of man who rescued seahorses|date=14 August 2009|accessdate=4 September 2009|newspaper=[[Irish Independent]]}}</ref>\n\n===Release===\nLinda Mulhall was released in 2018, having served over 12 years of a 15-year sentence.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.herald.ie/news/courts/scissor-sister-killer-linda-out-of-jail-and-back-on-city-streets-36457195.html|title=Scissor Sister killer Linda out of jail and back on city streets - Herald.ie|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:2005 in Ireland]]\n[[Category:2006 in Ireland]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Irish people convicted of manslaughter]]\n[[Category:Irish people convicted of murder]]\n[[Category:Irish prisoners sentenced to life imprisonment]]\n[[Category:Irish murderers]]\n[[Category:History of Dublin (city)]]\n[[Category:People from Dublin (city)]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:21st-century Irish criminals]]\n", "text_old": "{{Other uses|Scissor Sisters (disambiguation)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2013}}\n{{BLP sources|date=July 2018}}\n{{Infobox criminal\n|name= Linda and Charlotte Mulhall\n|image= \n|caption= \n|alias= The Scissor Sisters\n|birth_name = \n|birth_date= {{birth year and age|1975}} (Linda) <br/>c. 1983 (age 34-35) (Charlotte)\n|birth_place= [[Dublin]], [[Ireland]]\n|death_date= \n|cause=\n|victims= 1\n|beginyear=\n|endyear= \n| nationality = Irish\n| conviction_penalty = [[life imprisonment]] (Charlotte)<br/>15 years' imprisonment (Linda)\n| conviction_status = Incarcerated at [[Limerick Prison]] (Charlotte)<br/>Released (Linda)\n|apprehended= October 2006\n|conviction=  [[murder]] (Charlotte)<br/>[[manslaughter]] (Linda)\n|sentence    = \n|weapons     = [[Stanley knife]], hammer\n}}\n{{Location map | Ireland Central Dublin\n| relief   = yes\n| width    = 250\n| caption  = Location of the murder site in Dublin\n| lat_deg = 53.357842\n| lon_deg = -6.249823 \n| label   = 17 Richmond Cottages\n}}\n\n'''Linda and Charlotte Mulhall''' (also called the '''''Scissor Sisters''''' by the media) are sisters from [[Dublin]], Ireland, known for having killed and dismembered their mother's boyfriend, Farah Swaleh Noor, in March 2005. Noor was killed with a [[Stanley knife]] wielded by Charlotte and struck with a hammer by Linda following a confrontation with the sisters and their mother, Kathleen Mulhall. His head and penis were sliced off and the rest of his corpse dismembered by the women and dumped in [[Dublin]]'s [[Royal Canal]] where a piece of leg still wearing a sock was spotted floating near [[Croke Park]] ten days later.\n\nThe subsequent manhunt and the trial in October 2006 attracted intense media attention in Ireland as the true details of the crime slowly emerged. The sisters and their mother were arrested but released until Linda confessed to involvement in the crime. Kathleen Mulhall left the country at this point to live in England. When Charlotte and Linda were charged with murder in December 2005, their father, John Mulhall, hanged himself in [[Phoenix Park]]. As a result of the method they used to carry out the killing of Farah Swaleh Noor, Linda and Charlotte Mulhall were dubbed the ''Scissor Sisters'' by the media, after the pop rock band the [[Scissor Sisters]].<ref name=\"'Scissor' mother dated rapist after fleeing to UK\"/><ref name=\"Lengthy sentences for brutal sibling slayers\"/><ref name=\"Scissor Sister reveals head put in bins in Phoenix Park\"/> Justice [[Paul Carney]], presiding over the trial, said during sentencing that it was \"the most grotesque killing that has occurred in my professional lifetime\".<ref name=\"A horror story born out of dysfunction\"/> Charlotte Mulhall was given the mandatory life sentence and Linda Mulhall was given a 15-year sentence for manslaughter, with both being sent to [[D\u00f3chas Centre|Mountjoy Women's prison]] in Dublin.\n\nNoor's head and penis were never recovered,<ref name=\"Mulhall sister sentenced to life (2)\"/> although Linda later admitted they had put the head in rubbish bins around Phoenix Park. It was also thought that they carried the head by bus to [[Tallaght]] and buried it in a field, with Linda returning later to dig it up, carry it to another field using her son's schoolbag, smash it further with a hammer and bury it again. Linda attracted further media attention when she slit her wrists and was [[sectioned]]. Charlotte also attracted media attention when a photograph of her holding a knife to a male prisoner's throat was published; that action resulted in an increased security presence in all Irish prisons and Charlotte was moved from Mountjoy to [[Limerick]]. Kathleen Mulhall voluntarily returned to Ireland in February 2008 and faced several charges. She pleaded guilty to helping clean up the crime scene to conceal evidence and was sentenced to five years in prison in May 2009.\n\nThe case has resulted in several books and has been examined in at least one television series. It was said by the ''[[Irish Independent]]''{{'}}s legal affairs correspondent Dearbhail McDonald to have \"fuelled fears of ritual killings in Ireland\".<ref name=\"Lengthy sentences for brutal sibling slayers\"/>\n\n==Mulhall family background==\nThe Mulhalls were from Kilclare Gardens, a working class area in [[Tallaght]], south [[Dublin]]. Their parents John and Kathleen Mulhall raised a family of three boys and three girls. John Mulhall allegedly abused Kathleen. Their marriage broke down and Kathleen entered into a relationship with Farah Swaleh Noor in 2002. Noor moved into their family home with Kathleen, and John Mulhall took some of his children and moved out. He rented various accommodations in Dublin over a period of a year, then moved back into the home after Kathleen left and moved to [[Cork (city)|Cork]] with Noor. Kathleen and Noor returned to Dublin in 2004. Noor allegedly subjected Kathleen Mulhall to regular beatings.<ref name=\"Mulhall sister admits she hit victim with hammer\">{{cite web|url=http://www.breakingnews.ie/archives/2006/1018/ireland/cwidkfojeyql/#ixzz0Q31lk3sr|title=Mulhall sister admits she hit victim with hammer|date=18 October 2006|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=breakingnews.ie}}</ref><ref name=\"Composure breaks down as court hears litany of violence and abuse\">{{cite news|url=http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/ireland/2009/0506/1224245993737.html|title=Composure breaks down as court hears litany of violence and abuse|date=6 May 2009|accessdate=4 September 2009|newspaper=[[The Irish Times]]}}</ref>\n\n===Linda Mulhall===\nLinda Mulhall was 30 years old at the time of the killing. She was unemployed, had left school early and had four children. The relationship with the father of her children broke up<ref name=\"Fianc\u00e9 at the centre of 'Scissor Sister' attack\">{{cite news|author=Mick McCaffrey Security Editor |url=http://www.tribune.ie/archive/article/2007/jun/10/fiance-at-the-centre-of-scissor-sister-attack/ |title=Fianc\u00e9 at the centre of 'Scissor Sister' attack |date=10 June 2007 |accessdate=4 September 2009 |newspaper=[[Sunday Tribune]] }}{{dead link|date=June 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> and she got into another relationship with an individual called Wayne Kinsella who subsequently abused them, in one case beating the children with [[Electrical_conduit#Flexible | an electrical flex]]. The abuse was later investigated, and the children were taken into care by the social services, while Wayne Kinsella served a six-year prison sentence for his cruelty to the children. Kinsella himself had an extremely violent history, having been thrown out of school for violent behaviour, according to his elder sister, Donna. In a 2013 [[RT\u00c9 Radio]] interview, Donna Kinsella said that her brother Wayne was always an extremely violent person, even during his childhood, and stated that he used to beat members of his own family, including his parents, and had broken her jaw on one occasion.<ref name=\"Don't ever let my double-killer brother out of jail\">{{cite web|author=Conor Feehan Security Editor|url=http://www.herald.ie/news/dont-ever-let-my-doublekiller-brother-out-of-jail/|title='Don't ever let my double-killer brother out of jail'|date=22 May 2013|accessdate=14 September 2016|publisher=[[Herald]]}}</ref>  In May 1996, Kinsella received an eight-year prison sentence for the murder of a retired auctioneer, Thomas Foreman, who was killed while visiting his wife's grave in [[Glasnevin Cemetery]] in Dublin on 23 September 1995. In May 2012, Kinsella was jailed for life after being found guilty of the murder of 29-year-old Dubliner Adil Essalhi, who was stabbed to death in a field near [[Tyrrelstown]] on 6 January 2011. Kinsella claimed he murdered Adil Essalhi, because he believed that Mr. Essalhi had been involved in the killing of his younger brother, Lee Kinsella, who was shot dead in [[Finglas]] in May 2006.<ref name=\"Wayne Kinsella convicted of murder of Adel Essalhi in Tyrrelstown\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rte.ie/news/2012/0521/321799-wayne-kinsella-convicted-of-murder-of-adel-essalhi/|title=Wayne Kinsella convicted of murder of Adel Essalhi in Tyrrelstown|date=21 May 2012|accessdate=28 June 2019|website=[[RT\u00c9]]}}</ref> Wayne's sister Donna said Mr. Essalhi had nothing to do with Lee's death.<ref name=\"Don't ever let my double-killer brother out of jail\">{{cite web|author=Conor Feehan Security Editor|url=http://www.herald.ie/news/dont-ever-let-my-doublekiller-brother-out-of-jail/|title='Don't ever let my double-killer brother out of jail'|date=22 May 2013|accessdate=14 September 2016|publisher=[[Herald]]}}</ref> Wayne Kinsella's nephew Michael Kinsella would later be jailed for 15 years in May 2016 for helping his uncle kill Mr. Essalhi. Linda Mulhall, meanwhile, had a history of alcohol abuse and suffered from an addiction to heroin. She had one previous conviction in 1993 for [[larceny]].<ref name=\"A horror story born out of dysfunction\">{{cite news|author=CONOR LALLY, Crime Correspondent|url=http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/ireland/2009/0509/1224246189748.html|title=A horror story born out of dysfunction|date=9 May 2009|accessdate=4 September 2009|newspaper=[[The Irish Times]]}}</ref>\n\n===Charlotte Mulhall===\nCharlotte Mulhall was 21 years old when the killing took place. Like her sister, she had a history of drug and alcohol abuse. She had a number of minor previous convictions for criminal damage and public order offences and was charged with criminal damage and given the [[Probation]] Act in October 2005. She was also involved in prostitution.<ref name=\"Mulhall sister sentenced to life\">{{cite web|url=http://www.breakingnews.ie/ireland/?jp=CWIDQLSNKFAU&rss=yes|title=Mulhall sister sentenced to life|date=4 December 2006|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=breakingnews.ie}}</ref>\n\nDuring their trial, [[garda\u00ed]] described the girls' upbringing as \"troubled and tough\".<ref name=\"Verdicts returned in canal murder trial\">{{cite web|url=http://www.choicefm.ie/news_details.php|title=Verdicts returned in canal murder trial|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=[[Choice FM]]}}</ref>\n\n==Farah Swaleh Noor==\n<!-- [[File:Farahswaleh.jpg|right|180px|thumb|Photograph of Farah Swaleh Noor released during the garda investigation into his death]] -->\n\n{{Infobox person\n|name=Farah Swaleh Noor\n| birth_date = 1965\n| birth_place = [[Mombasa]], \n [[Kenya]]\n| death_place= [[Northside, Dublin|Summerhill]], [[Dublin]], Ireland\n| death_date = 20 March 2005 (aged 40)\n| body_discovered = [[Royal Canal (Ireland)|Royal Canal]]\n| occupation = unemployed\n}}\n\nFarah Swaleh Noor was 40 years old at the time of his death. He arrived in Ireland in December 1996, claiming to be a [[Somalis|Somali]] called \"Sheilila Salim\" whose family had been killed in [[Mogadishu]] during the [[Somali Civil War]]. Subsequent investigations revealed that he was in fact [[Kenya]]n and that his family was still alive. Farah was ethnically [[Somalis|Somali]]. The [[Department of Justice and Equality|Department of Justice, Equality and Law Reform]] ordered that he be deported but he appealed and was granted Irish citizenship in March 1999 on grounds he became the father of an Irish-born child. He had four previous convictions for offences including [[Substance intoxication|intoxication]], threatening and abusive behaviour and assault. In 1997, he [[rape]]d a mentally disabled 16-year-old Chinese girl. She later gave birth to a son. Two other women had children by him and both described having been raped by him.<ref name=\"Woman tells canal body murder trial of rape hell\">{{cite news|author=Eleanor Burnhill|url=http://www.independent.ie/national-news/woman-tells-canal-body-murder-trial-of-rape-hell-74802.html|title=Woman tells canal body murder trial of rape hell|date=24 October 2006|accessdate=4 September 2009|newspaper=[[Irish Independent]]}}</ref> Noor had faced eight charges of disorder and assault, one involving a sexual assault in which a knife was found at the scene by garda\u00ed. He was convicted on three occasions but never served time in jail. Noor lived in a number of areas in Dublin, including [[D\u00fan Laoghaire]] and [[Firhouse]], as well as the inner city before moving in with Kathleen Mulhall. Garda\u00ed described him as being particularly [[Domestic violence|violent towards women]].<ref name=\"African drifter died after drink and drugs bender\">{{cite news|author=Eleanor Burnhill|url=http://www.independent.ie/lifestyle/african-drifter-died-after--drink-and-drugs-bender-1466364.html|title=African drifter died after drink and drugs bender|date=24 October 2006|accessdate=4 September 2008|newspaper=[[Irish Independent]]}}</ref>\n\n==Events surrounding the killing==\nThe killing took place at a flat Kathleen Mulhall was renting in a house on Richmond Cottages, [[Summerhill, Dublin|Summerhill]], on 20 March 2005. This was on the bank holiday of [[Saint Patrick's Day|Saint Patrick's weekend]].<ref name=\"Mulhall sister sentenced to life (1)\">{{cite web|url=http://www.breakingnews.ie/ireland/?jp=CWIDQLSNKFAU&rss=yes#ixzz0PsHAZfe|title=Mulhall sister sentenced to life|date=4 December 2006|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=breakingnews.ie}}</ref>\n\n===Build-up to the killing===\nOn the day of the killing, Linda, Charlotte, their mother and Farah Swaleh Noor had been drinking heavily in Dublin city centre. Farah bought [[vodka]] and Kathleen Mulhall purchased [[Coca-Cola]] which they drank as they walked around the city before stopping on the [[River Liffey]] Boardwalk where Charlotte and her mother took [[Ecstasy (drug)|ecstasy tablets]]. They returned to Kathleen Mulhall's flat where the women took ecstasy. Kathleen Mulhall crushed a tablet into the victim's drink so they were \"all on\" the same \"buzz\".<ref name=\"Mulhall sister sentenced to life (2)\">{{cite web|url=http://www.breakingnews.ie/ireland/?jp=CWIDQLSNKFAU&rss=yes#ixzz0PwMQ2LM2|title=Mulhall sister sentenced to life|date=4 December 2006|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=breakingnews.ie}}</ref>\n\n===Death of Farah Swaleh Noor===\nLinda and Noor were sitting on a two-seater couch with Charlotte sitting on the arm, when Noor started touching Linda in a sexual way. He spoke into her ear, put his arms around her waist and refused to let her go. Kathleen then started screaming at him and a verbal altercation took place where Kathleen Mulhall was alleged to have instructed them to \"just kill him for me\". Charlotte picked up a [[Stanley knife]] and struck Noor across the throat, inflicting a wound that sent him to the ground. Linda then picked up a hammer and hit him on the head a number of times. Their mother looked on but did not participate. Noor was stabbed at least 27 times. It may have been more, but [[pathologist]]s had no opportunity to examine the full body.<ref name=\"From murder to manslaughter\">{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/national-news/from-murder-to-manslaughter-75843.html|title=From murder to manslaughter|date=30 October 2006|accessdate=4 September 2009|newspaper=[[Irish Independent]]}}</ref>\n\n===Dismemberment and disposal of the corpse===\nLinda and Charlotte then dragged Noor's corpse into the bathroom where they began to dismember the remains. Noor's head, [[limb (anatomy)|limb]]s and [[penis]] were severed using a kitchen knife and hammer. They put towels over his legs to stem the flow of blood. The dismemberment took a number of hours and the body parts were placed in black plastic bags and a sports bag before being disposed of in the [[Royal Canal]]. This took the three women several trips. They decided not to throw the head in to prevent identification. The head was brought by bus to Tallaght where they walked through [[The Square, Tallaght|The Square Shopping Centre]] to Tymon North Park. They walked to where Charlotte dug a hole with a knife to bury the head. Kathleen Mulhall threw the knives and the hammer into a nearby pond. A number of days later, Linda Mulhall allegedly returned to the park and dug up the head. Using her son's schoolbag, she transferred it to a field in the Killinarden Estate, Tallaght, where she broke it up with a hammer before burying it again.<ref name=\"Mulhall sister admits she hit victim with hammer\">{{cite web|url=http://www.breakingnews.ie/archives/2006/1018/ireland/cwidkfojeyql/#ixzz0Px1qkyR3|title=Mulhall sister admits she hit victim with hammer|date=18 October 2006|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=breakingnews.ie}}</ref>\n\n==Garda S\u00edoch\u00e1na investigation==\nThe killing only came to light ten days later when Noor's leg, with a sock on the end, was seen floating in the canal, a few hundred yards from [[Croke Park]]. [[Garda Water Unit|Garda sub-aqua divers]] retrieved most of the rest of his body in seven parts. Garda\u00ed traced his identity through media appeals. Noor was only identified when someone recognised a T-shirt on the recovered torso. That key witness, a Somalian man who was the first to connect the missing Noor with the three Mulhall women, was paid a \"substantial\" reward by Crimestoppers.<ref name=\"Gardai seek mother of killer sisters\"/> Noor's head and penis were never found.<ref name=\"Mulhall sister sentenced to life (2)\"/>\n\nThe sisters and their parents were arrested in August but denied any knowledge of the killing. A number of weeks later Linda contacted investigating officers admitting her involvement. Garda\u00ed took a voluntary statement from her at her home in Tallaght in August 2005. Until this, Garda\u00ed had been making limited progress in the case. When Garda\u00ed searched the Mulhall flat in Summerhill, they found bloodstains that were later confirmed to match Noor's [[DNA]].<ref name=\"Mulhall sister admits she hit victim with hammer\">{{cite web|url=http://www.breakingnews.ie/archives/2006/1018/ireland/cwidkfojeyql/#ixzz0Q37l4sUO|title=Mulhall sister admits she hit victim with hammer|date=18 October 2006|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=breakingnews.ie}}</ref><ref name=\"Gardai seek mother of killer sisters\">{{cite news|author=Enda Leahy|url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/world/ireland/article616939.ece|title=Gardai seek mother of killer sisters|date=29 October 2006|accessdate=4 September 2009|newspaper=[[The Sunday Times]]}}</ref> After Linda's confession, Kathleen Mulhall fled the country in September 2005 and garda\u00ed were unable to locate her again until January 2008. She was living in England.<ref name=\"'Scissor' mother dated rapist after fleeing to UK\">{{cite news|author=Mick McCaffrey and Mark Hilliard |url=http://www.tribune.ie/news/article/2009/may/10/scissor-mother-dated-rapist-after-fleeing-to-uk/ |title='Scissor' mother dated rapist after fleeing to UK |date=10 May 2009 |accessdate=4 September 2009 |newspaper=[[Sunday Tribune]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090515084041/http://www.tribune.ie/news/article/2009/may/10/scissor-mother-dated-rapist-after-fleeing-to-uk/ |archivedate=15 May 2009 }}</ref>\n\n==Court cases==\n===Murder trial of Linda and Charlotte Mulhall===\nLinda and Charlotte were both charged with murder and pleaded not guilty in the [[High Court (Ireland)|Central Criminal Court]]. Their trial took place in October 2006 with Linda Mulhall being found guilty of [[manslaughter]] while her sister Charlotte was found guilty of the murder of Noor. Linda's jury accepted her defence of provocation.\n\nCharlotte Mulhall was given the mandatory life sentence and Linda Mulhall was given a 15-year sentence for manslaughter. The judge argued that Linda, a heroin addict, had initially tried to halt the trial by refusing to take [[methadone]]. Leave to appeal was refused for both sentences.<ref name=\"Mulhall sister sentenced to life\">{{cite web|url=http://www.breakingnews.ie/ireland/?jp=CWIDQLSNKFAU&rss=yes#ixzz0PwMD7wOo|title=Mulhall sister sentenced to life|date=4 December 2006|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=breakingnews.ie}}</ref><ref name=\"Sisters sentenced over Noor death\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rte.ie/news/2006/1204/noorf.html|title=Sisters sentenced over Noor death|date=4 December 2008|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=[[Raidi\u00f3 Teilif\u00eds \u00c9ireann|RT\u00c9]]}}</ref>\n\nLinda Mulhall appealed the severity of her sentence<ref name=\"D.P.P.-v- Linda Mulhall\">{{cite web|url=http://www.courts.ie/Judgments.nsf/23fd4a34bad801d980256ec50047a0a8/67a09b519186ab01802573ee00523b66?OpenDocument&Highlight=0,mulhall|title=D.P.P.-v- Linda Mulhall|date=8 February 2008|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=[[Criminal Court Record of Appeals]]}}</ref> on the grounds that it was passed without psychiatric and probation reports. This appeal failed, with the [[Court of Criminal Appeal]] finding the sentence to be appropriate.<ref name=\"Mulhall loses appeal over jail sentence\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rte.ie/news/2008/0421/noor.html?rss|title=Mulhall loses appeal over jail sentence|date=21 April 2008|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=[[Raidi\u00f3 Teilif\u00eds \u00c9ireann|RT\u00c9]]}}</ref>\n\nCharlotte Mulhall requested leave to appeal her conviction on the grounds that Justice Carney had put pressure on the jury to reach a verdict even though the foreman had indicated they were deadlocked.<ref name=\"Charlotte Mulhall begins murder conviction appeal\">{{cite news|url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/breaking-news/ireland/charlotte-mulhall-begins-murder-conviction-appeal-13392822.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130420073056/http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/breaking-news/ireland/charlotte-mulhall-begins-murder-conviction-appeal-13392822.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=20 April 2013 |title=Charlotte Mulhall begins murder conviction appeal |date=11 March 2008 |accessdate=4 September 2009 |newspaper=[[The Belfast Telegraph]] }}</ref> This failed on the grounds that the defence did not raise objections to the comments during the trial and the fact that the jury was not affected by any alleged undue pressure to reach a verdict.<ref name=\"Charlotte Mulhall denied leave to appeal\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rte.ie/news/2008/0311/noorfs.html|title=Charlotte Mulhall denied leave to appeal|date=11 March 2008|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=[[Raidi\u00f3 Teilif\u00eds \u00c9ireann|RT\u00c9]]}}</ref>\n\n===Court case against Kathleen Mulhall===\nKathleen Mulhall voluntarily returned to Ireland in February 2008 and was charged with, among other offences, two counts of giving false information to garda\u00ed about Noor's whereabouts, and withholding information which she \"knew or believed\" would be of assistance in prosecuting her daughters for Noor's murder. She was also charged with impeding an arrest in the murder investigation. She pleaded guilty to helping to clean up the crime scene to conceal evidence.<ref name=\"Mulhall cleaned up murder crime scene\">{{cite news|url=http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/breaking/2009/0505/breaking52.htm|title=Mulhall cleaned up murder crime scene|date=5 May 2009|accessdate=4 September 2009|newspaper=[[The Irish Times]]}}</ref><ref name=\"Scissor Sisters' mum faces 10 new charges\">{{cite news|author=Fiach Kelly|url=http://www.independent.ie/national-news/scissor-sisters-mum-faces-10-new-charges-1321949.html|title=Scissor Sisters' mum faces 10 new charges|date=20 March 2008|accessdate=4 September 2009|newspaper=[[Irish Independent]]}}</ref> Kathleen Mulhall was sentenced to five years in prison in May 2009.<ref name=\"Mulhall sentenced for cleaning crime scene\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rte.ie/news/2009/0508/mulhallk.html|title=Mulhall sentenced for cleaning crime scene|date=8 May 2009|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=[[Raidi\u00f3 Teilif\u00eds \u00c9ireann|RT\u00c9]]}}</ref>\n\n==Fallout and aftermath==\n===Mulhall family===\nThe girls' father, John Mulhall, hanged himself in [[Phoenix Park]] when his daughters were charged with the killing in December 2005. He was not believed to have been involved in the killing.<ref name=\"Lengthy sentences for brutal sibling slayers\">{{cite news|author=Dearbhail McDonaldLegal Affairs|url=http://www.independent.ie/national-news/lengthy-sentences-for-brutal-sibling-slayers-63017.html#Scene_1|title=Lengthy sentences for brutal sibling slayers|date=12 May 2006|accessdate=4 September 2009|newspaper=[[Irish Independent]]}}</ref>\n\nLinda Mulhall turned to alcohol and slashed her arms, causing her to spend over a week in a psychiatric hospital.<ref name=\"Mulhall sister admits she hit victim with hammer\">{{cite web|url=http://www.breakingnews.ie/archives/2006/1018/ireland/cwidkfojeyql/#ixzz0Q31HAuTe|title=Mulhall sister admits she hit victim with hammer|date=18 October 2006|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=breakingnews.ie}}</ref> In April 2009, she claimed to fellow inmates that she had in fact smashed Noor's head and distributed the fragments in rubbish bins in the [[Phoenix Park]].<ref name=\"Scissor Sister reveals head put in bins in Phoenix Park\">{{cite news|author=Cormac Looney |url=http://www.herald.ie/national-news/city-news/scissor-sister-reveals-head-put-in-bins-in-phoenix-park-1707808.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130217193754/http://www.herald.ie/national-news/city-news/scissor-sister-reveals-head-put-in-bins-in-phoenix-park-1707808.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=17 February 2013 |title=Scissor Sister reveals head put in bins in Phoenix Park |date=14 April 2009 |accessdate=4 September 2009 |newspaper=[[Evening Herald]] }}</ref> This first disclosure of where Noor's head had ended up, was referred to as \"the final secret of the Scissor Sisters\" by Cormac Looney in the ''[[Evening Herald]]''.<ref name=\"Scissor Sister reveals head put in bins in Phoenix Park\"/>\n\nCharlotte caused a further national controversy in 2008 when photographs of her jokingly holding a knife to the throat of a male prisoner in [[Mountjoy Prison]] were leaked to the press. As a result, security in Irish prisons was increased.<ref name=\"Prison Service to up security over Scissor Sister pictures\">{{cite news|author=Shane Phelan|url=http://www.independent.ie/national-news/prison-service-to-up-security-over-scissor-sister-pictures-1461724.html#Scene_1|title=Prison Service to up security over Scissor Sister pictures|date=23 August 2008|accessdate=4 September 2009|newspaper=[[Irish Independent]]}}</ref> and Charlotte was moved to [[Limerick Prison]], the only other Irish prison to contain a women's unit.\n\nThe girls' brother, James Mulhall, pleaded guilty to the robbery of two prostitutes, claiming he robbed the women to support his own six children and his sister Linda's four children whom he took on after she was jailed.<ref name=\"Two men get five years for robbing prostitutes\">{{cite web|url=http://www.breakingnews.ie/archives/2008/0401/ireland/mhojojgbkfmh/|title=Two men get five years for robbing prostitutes|date=1 April 2008|accessdate=4 September 2009|publisher=breakingnews.ie}}</ref>\n\n===Books===\nThe case received a high amount of attention due to the grotesque and macabre nature of the crime. This led to the sisters being dubbed \"The Scissor Sisters\" by the media after the [[Scissor Sisters|pop group]] from New York, USA.\n\nSeveral books were written on the circumstances surrounding the death of Farah Swaleh Noor:\n*''The Torso in the Canal''&nbsp;\u2014 John Mooney (Maverick House, {{ISBN|978-1-905379-38-5}})\n*''The Irish Scissor Sisters''&nbsp;\u2014 Mick McCaffrey (Merlin Publishing, {{ISBN|1-903582-72-5}})<ref name=\"'Scissor' mother dated rapist after fleeing to UK\"/> McCaffrey covered the case for the ''[[Sunday Tribune]]''.<ref name=\"'Scissor' mother dated rapist after fleeing to UK\"/>\n\n===Television series===\nThe 2009 RT\u00c9 television series ''Killers'' featured the Mulhall sisters.<ref name=\"Lifestyle rubbish and lame-brained comedy jostle for position with four-part tale of man who rescued seahorses\">{{cite news|author=John Boland|url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/tv-radio/lifestyle-rubbish-and-lamebrained-comedy-jostle-for-position-with-fourpart-tale-of-man-who-rescued-seahorses-1859824.html|title=Lifestyle rubbish and lame-brained comedy jostle for position with four-part tale of man who rescued seahorses|date=14 August 2009|accessdate=4 September 2009|newspaper=[[Irish Independent]]}}</ref>\n\n===Release===\nLinda Mulhall was released in 2018, having served over 12 years of a 15-year sentence.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.herald.ie/news/courts/scissor-sister-killer-linda-out-of-jail-and-back-on-city-streets-36457195.html|title=Scissor Sister killer Linda out of jail and back on city streets - Herald.ie|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:2005 in Ireland]]\n[[Category:2006 in Ireland]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Irish people convicted of manslaughter]]\n[[Category:Irish people convicted of murder]]\n[[Category:Irish prisoners sentenced to life imprisonment]]\n[[Category:Irish murderers]]\n[[Category:History of Dublin (city)]]\n[[Category:People from Dublin (city)]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:21st-century Irish criminals]]\n", "name_user": "Quebec99", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fix duplicate ref names \u2013You can help!", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scissor_Sisters_(convicted_killers)"}
{"title_page": "Varun Toorkey", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian actor}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Varun Toorkey\n| image              = varuntoorkey.jpg\n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = Varun Toorkey\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age |df=y|1990|01|08}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/india/love-is-in-the-air-for-varun-and-surbhi/articleshow/56521089.cms|title=Varun: love is in the air for Varun and Surbhi|date=2017-01-14|website=[[Times of India]]|language=en-US|access-date=2017-10-27}}</ref><ref name=interview/>\n| birth_place        = [[Bombay]], [[Maharashtra]], India\n| citizenship        = [[India]]n\n| occupation         = Actor, Model\n| years_active       = 2006\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Varun Toorkey''' is an Indian television actor known for portraying Shaad Khan in ''[[Qubool Hai]]'' and Tushar Mallick in ''[[Humko Tumse Ho Gaya Hai Pyaar Kya Karein]].''\n\n==Personal life==\nBorn and brought up in Mumbai, Toorkey belongs to [[Parsi]] community.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tellychakkar.com/photo/slideshow/happy-navroz-parsis-who-made-it-big-tv-160817/?slide=1&page=1|title=Happy Navroz: Parsis who made it big on TV|date=2016-08-17|website=Tellychakkar.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-10-27}}</ref>\n\nHe did his schooling in Bombay Cambridge School, [[JB Nagar]], Mumbai and graduated from [[Mithibai College|Mithibai college]] with a B.com degree.\n\nToorkey has attained training in acting from [[Anupam Kher]]'s ''Actor Prepares''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tellychakkar.com/tv/tv-news/newbie-varun-toorkey-enter-colors-uttaran|title=Newbie Varun Toorkey to enter Colors' Uttaran|last=Team|first=Tellychakkar|website=Tellychakkar.com|access-date=2016-06-17}}</ref>\n\nHe is the best friend of Indian television actress Surbhi Chandna and they are dating each other\n\n==Career==\nToorkey was just 16 years of age when he got his first break into the industry, in a [[compilation album]] called [[Ustad and the Divas|Ustad and the divas]]. In that album, he acted as a computer professional in the song [[Leja Leja Re]] which was sung by [[Shreya Ghoshal]] and [[Ustad Sultan Khan]]. The album released in 2006.<ref name=interview>[https://youtube.com/watch?v=1KVgHSJCAps Varun Toorkey Interview - Bataz Buzz]</ref>\n\nHe made his television debut in 2013, playing Sankrant in [[Colors TV]]'s ''[[Uttaran]]''.\n\nIn 2015, he played Shaad Aftaab Khan in [[Zee TV]]'s ''[[Qubool Hai]]'' opposite [[Surbhi Jyoti]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/qubool-hai-take-20-years-leap-karanvir-bohra-aka-aahil-be-axed-640618|title='Qubool Hai' to Take 20-Year Leap; Karanvir Bohra aka Aahil to be Axed?|website=International Business Times, India Edition|language=en|access-date=2016-06-17}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Toorkey played Tushar Malik in ''[[Humko Tumse Ho Gaya Hai Pyaar Kya Karein]]'' opposite [[Ishani Sharma]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/television/210816/we-talk-over-the-phone-after-shoots-varun-toorkey.html|title=We talk over the phone after shoots: Varun Toorkey|website=Deccan Chronicle|language=en}}</ref>\n\nFrom 2017 to 2018, he portrayed Anant Singh Baghel in ''[[Saam Daam Dand Bhed (TV series)|Saam Daam Dand Bhed]]''.\n\nIn March 2019, he made a cameo appearance in ''[[Yeh Rishta Kya Kehlata Hai]]'' playing Rishabh opposite [[Shivangi Joshi]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/television/soaps/story/yeh-rishta-kya-kehlata-hai-spoiler-a-new-man-to-enter-naira-s-life-1462500-2019-02-22|title=Yeh Rishta Kya Kehlata Hai spoiler: A new man to enter Naira's life|website=India Today|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Show\n!Role\n!Ref\n|-\n|2013&ndash;15\n|''[[Uttaran]]''\n|Sankrant Chatterjee\n|\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[Qubool Hai]]''\n|Shaad Aftab Khan\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/TV-show-Qubool-Hai-to-undergo-a-revamp/articleshow/46309269.cms|title=TV show Qubool Hai to undergo a revamp - Times of India|website=The Times of India|access-date=2016-06-17}}</ref>\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Humko Tumse Ho Gaya Hai Pyaar Kya Karein]]''\n|Tushar Mallick\n|\n|-\n|2017&ndash;18\n|''[[Saam Daam Dand Bhed (TV series)|Saam Daam Dand Bhed]]''\n|Anant Singh Baghel\n|\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[Yeh Rishta Kya Kehlata Hai]]''\n|Rishabh\n|Cameo\n|}\n\n===Music Videos===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Album\n!Song\n!Reference\n|-\n|2006\n|[[Ustad & the Divas|Ustad and the Divas]]\n|[[Leja Leja Re]]\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lyricsbogie.com/albums/ustad-the-divas-2006/leja-leja-re.html|title=Leja Leja Re - Latest Hindi Songs Lyrics {{!}} Hindi Movie Song Lyrics {{!}} LyricsBogie|date=2012-10-17|website=Latest Hindi Songs Lyrics {{!}} Hindi Movie Song Lyrics {{!}} LyricsBogie|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-17}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Toorkey, Varun}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Indian male television actors]]\n[[Category:Indian male models]]\n[[Category:Parsi people from Mumbai]]\n[[Category:Indian Zoroastrians]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Mumbai]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Hindi television]]\n[[Category:Parsi people]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian actor}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Varun Toorkey\n| image              = varuntoorkey.jpg\n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = Varun Toorkey\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age |df=y|1990|01|08}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/india/love-is-in-the-air-for-varun-and-surbhi/articleshow/56521089.cms|title=Varun: love is in the air for Varun and Surbhi|date=2017-01-14|website=[[Times of India]]|language=en-US|access-date=2017-10-27}}</ref><ref name=interview/>\n| birth_place        = [[Bombay]], [[Maharashtra]], India\n| citizenship        = [[India]]n\n| occupation         = Actor, Model\n| years_active       = 2006\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Varun Toorkey''' is an Indian television actor known for portraying Shaad Khan in ''[[Qubool Hai]]'' and Tushar Mallick in ''[[Humko Tumse Ho Gaya Hai Pyaar Kya Karein]].''\n\n==Personal life==\nBorn and brought up in Mumbai, Toorkey belongs to [[Parsi]] community.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tellychakkar.com/photo/slideshow/happy-navroz-parsis-who-made-it-big-tv-160817/?slide=1&page=1|title=Happy Navroz: Parsis who made it big on TV|date=2016-08-17|website=Tellychakkar.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-10-27}}</ref>\n\nHe did his schooling in Bombay Cambridge School, [[JB Nagar]], Mumbai and graduated from [[Mithibai College|Mithibai college]] with a B.com degree.\n\nToorkey has attained training in acting from [[Anupam Kher]]'s ''Actor Prepares''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tellychakkar.com/tv/tv-news/newbie-varun-toorkey-enter-colors-uttaran|title=Newbie Varun Toorkey to enter Colors' Uttaran|last=Team|first=Tellychakkar|website=Tellychakkar.com|access-date=2016-06-17}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nToorkey was just 16 years of age when he got his first break into the industry, in a [[compilation album]] called [[Ustad and the Divas|Ustad and the divas]]. In that album, he acted as a computer professional in the song [[Leja Leja Re]] which was sung by [[Shreya Ghoshal]] and [[Ustad Sultan Khan]]. The album released in 2006.<ref name=interview>[https://youtube.com/watch?v=1KVgHSJCAps Varun Toorkey Interview - Bataz Buzz]</ref>\n\nHe made his television debut in 2013, playing Sankrant in [[Colors TV]]'s ''[[Uttaran]]''.\n\nIn 2015, he played Shaad Aftaab Khan in [[Zee TV]]'s ''[[Qubool Hai]]'' opposite [[Surbhi Jyoti]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/qubool-hai-take-20-years-leap-karanvir-bohra-aka-